WEBVTT

00:00.578 --> 00:02.695
<i>Previously, on "Bitten"...</i>

00:02.711 --> 00:05.011
Gorgeous dog. Clay...

00:05.013 --> 00:06.880
(Yelling in pain)

00:06.882 --> 00:08.814
They've been watching us, in Toronto.

00:08.816 --> 00:10.583
It's not just you the Mutts are after.

00:10.585 --> 00:12.051
It's Elena.

00:12.053 --> 00:14.053
James: I want them all dead.
All except her.

00:14.055 --> 00:16.489
Don't worry, Daniel.
You'll get your prize.

00:16.491 --> 00:18.391
(Deadbolt clattering)

00:20.294 --> 00:22.128
Shh, shh.
(Panicked breath)

00:24.530 --> 00:27.199
(Mixed grunts)

00:27.201 --> 00:30.701
( ♪ )

00:33.540 --> 00:36.075
(Groaning) Rachel: Logan?

00:37.577 --> 00:40.412
- Take me to Stonehaven.
- Okay, okay.

00:40.414 --> 00:41.846
(Grunting)

00:41.848 --> 00:44.116
I think we're alone now.

00:44.118 --> 00:47.285
(Snarling)

00:47.287 --> 00:49.554
Ahh, aaah!

00:50.856 --> 00:53.391
(Howl of rage)

00:55.361 --> 00:57.895
(Bones cracking)

00:59.297 --> 01:01.666
In a better world,

01:01.668 --> 01:03.701
I would have married you.

01:08.007 --> 01:10.008
(Panting)

01:10.010 --> 01:12.710
( ♪ )

01:12.712 --> 01:14.345
(Unlock signal beeps)

01:17.382 --> 01:19.650
(Tires screeching)

01:22.954 --> 01:25.356
- Nick.
- Thank God you're all right.

01:25.358 --> 01:26.723
We have to go.

01:26.725 --> 01:28.825
Olson stabbed Philip.
I called an ambulance.

01:28.827 --> 01:31.695
The police probably aren't far behind.

01:31.697 --> 01:33.897
Jeremy, they took Clay.

01:33.899 --> 01:36.133
We were just at Logan's apartment.
They attacked there too.

01:36.135 --> 01:37.801
Logan and Rachel are missing.

01:37.803 --> 01:39.703
We have to get to Clay. If we split
up, we can track the Mutts...

01:39.705 --> 01:41.337
The Mutts could be anywhere by now.

01:41.339 --> 01:42.873
No, we have to do something!

01:42.875 --> 01:45.175
Listen, Santos is dangerous.
He's not a fool.

01:45.177 --> 01:47.277
They're not going to kill him
before they get what they need.

01:47.279 --> 01:49.245
You're willing to risk
Clay's life on that?

01:49.247 --> 01:50.746
Because I'm not.

01:50.748 --> 01:52.515
We need to work together on this, Elena.

01:52.517 --> 01:54.950
If they catch you, there'll
be no further need for Clay.

01:54.952 --> 01:57.720
Now we will get him back, but
we need to keep you safe.

01:57.722 --> 02:00.156
Nick will go back to Stonehaven with you

02:00.158 --> 02:02.458
and we can prepare for
Santos' next move.

02:06.897 --> 02:10.396
( ♪ )

02:14.105 --> 02:16.038
(Laboured breathing)

02:21.578 --> 02:22.977
(Crackling)

02:26.349 --> 02:28.116
Ready to make some noise, Clayton?

02:30.119 --> 02:31.753
(Buzzing)

02:31.755 --> 02:32.921
(Soft grunt)

02:32.923 --> 02:35.691
You're going to need a bigger battery.

02:35.693 --> 02:37.692
What I don't need is your
roadside assistance.

02:37.694 --> 02:39.393
Call Marsten and LeBlanc.

02:39.395 --> 02:41.629
Let them know we're here.

02:41.631 --> 02:43.664
Getting someone to talk is child's play.

02:43.666 --> 02:46.868
The real trick is convincing
them to stay quiet.

02:46.870 --> 02:49.237
Well, this is about more than
just getting him to talk.

02:49.239 --> 02:50.905
It's about respect.

02:52.241 --> 02:54.842
(Buzzing)
(Grunting)

02:54.844 --> 02:56.577
(Yelling)

02:57.679 --> 02:59.680
You can call it respect if you want,

02:59.682 --> 03:02.082
but it sure looks like revenge to me.

03:06.355 --> 03:07.988
(Dialling beeps)

03:09.390 --> 03:11.524
(Cell phone chiming)

03:11.526 --> 03:13.227
Elena: Hello.

03:13.229 --> 03:15.495
Santos: (On speakerphone)
<i>Nice to hear your voice, Elena.</i>

03:15.497 --> 03:17.631
<i>- We need to talk.</i>
- If you hurt Clay,

03:17.633 --> 03:19.699
I swear I will make you
live to regret it.

03:19.701 --> 03:22.335
I have a proposition to make.

03:22.337 --> 03:24.972
And trust me when I say this
is in your best interests.

03:24.974 --> 03:27.774
<i>Meet me at the Bear Valley
Diner tomorrow at noon.</i>

03:27.776 --> 03:29.842
<i>And forget about bringing the Pack.</i>

03:29.844 --> 03:32.345
<i>I'll smell them before</i>
<i>they enter the door.</i>

03:32.347 --> 03:35.014
And just in case you don't
think I'm serious...

03:36.484 --> 03:38.117
(Buzzing)

03:38.119 --> 03:39.452
(Yelling in pain)

03:39.454 --> 03:41.421
Stop it, okay?

03:42.555 --> 03:44.556
I'll meet you at noon.

03:45.659 --> 03:48.394
I look forward to seeing you.

03:48.396 --> 03:50.362
I think...

03:50.364 --> 03:51.998
that got her attention.

03:54.134 --> 03:56.435
(Buzzing)
(Yelling)

03:56.437 --> 03:58.570
(Grunting)

04:04.110 --> 04:07.610
( ♪ )

