04:41.158 --> 04:44.658
( ♪ )

04:49.621 --> 04:50.922
(Sniffing)

04:50.925 --> 04:52.094
Please tell me

04:52.096 --> 04:54.296
I'm not detecting a faint
whiff of Clayton Danvers

04:54.298 --> 04:56.331
above the layers of horse manure.

04:56.333 --> 04:58.333
I hope you haven't done
anything rash with him.

04:58.335 --> 05:00.069
He's tied up and drugged for now.

05:00.071 --> 05:01.604
I see you've got the stuff.

05:01.606 --> 05:03.371
Walked into the local emergency room.

05:03.373 --> 05:06.541
Took what I needed before
anyone knew I was there.

05:06.543 --> 05:08.076
You see?

05:08.078 --> 05:09.777
No worries where
Clayton Danvers is concerned.

05:09.779 --> 05:11.446
I'm not worried about him.

05:11.448 --> 05:13.381
I'm worried about what we're
going to do with him.

05:13.383 --> 05:15.117
Thomas, go check on Olson.

05:15.119 --> 05:18.019
Make sure he's behaving himself.

05:18.021 --> 05:20.154
When did I become the
diddler's babysitter?

05:21.456 --> 05:22.890
Do as you're told.

05:28.964 --> 05:30.632
What happened at Logan's?

05:30.634 --> 05:32.566
In the heat of the moment,
Mr. LeBlanc went rogue.

05:32.568 --> 05:34.736
Proved himself unreliable.

05:34.738 --> 05:37.771
Suffice to say, Logan Jonsen
lives to howl another day.

05:37.773 --> 05:40.541
I gather things went poorly on your end.

05:40.543 --> 05:43.477
Olson didn't kill Elena's
boyfriend as planned.

05:43.479 --> 05:46.547
Now the guy can I.D.
Olson to the police.

05:46.549 --> 05:48.616
And I was going to take Elena

05:48.618 --> 05:51.084
as collateral to lure Jeremy.

05:51.086 --> 05:52.552
Unfortunately, she didn't show up.

05:52.554 --> 05:55.355
So I took Clay instead.

05:55.357 --> 05:57.457
I thought the plan was to cull the herd

05:57.459 --> 05:58.959
and force Jeremy to relinquish control.

05:58.961 --> 06:01.594
But here we are talking about Elena,

06:01.596 --> 06:03.229
a name that seems to
come up more frequently

06:03.231 --> 06:04.430
than Jeremy's of late.

06:04.432 --> 06:06.099
What does it matter,

06:06.101 --> 06:09.001
as long as we all get
what we want in the end?

06:14.408 --> 06:16.576
(Remote phone ringing)

06:19.780 --> 06:21.681
- I came as soon as I could.
- Hi.

06:22.749 --> 06:24.584
Glad you're here.

06:24.586 --> 06:26.052
What happened?

06:26.054 --> 06:28.187
It was a home invasion.
Philip was stabbed.

06:28.189 --> 06:29.955
They just took him in for surgery.

06:29.957 --> 06:32.591
- Oh, my... God...
- He's going to be fine.

06:32.593 --> 06:34.226
- Dia...
- Mom.

06:34.228 --> 06:35.427
He'll be okay.

06:35.429 --> 06:38.530
W... What about Elena? W... Is she okay?

06:38.532 --> 06:40.232
I don't know.

06:40.234 --> 06:41.667
She's, um...

06:41.669 --> 06:43.802
she's not answering her phone.

06:45.905 --> 06:47.673
Jeremy: It's a trap.

06:47.675 --> 06:49.308
I'm not letting you meet with Santos.

06:49.310 --> 06:51.176
I'm not asking for your permission.

06:51.178 --> 06:52.911
He specifically asked to speak with me.

06:52.913 --> 06:54.979
He's right, Elena. It's too dangerous.

06:54.981 --> 06:57.482
If I don't go to that meeting,

06:57.484 --> 06:59.617
Santos is going to start
shipping Clay home

06:59.619 --> 07:02.420
one piece at a time,
just like Dennis Stillwell.

07:02.422 --> 07:05.223
Elena, I said no.
(Car approaching)

07:08.761 --> 07:10.095
It's Logan.

07:12.765 --> 07:14.099
Rachel's with him.

07:16.568 --> 07:17.801
I'll get the first aid kit.

07:17.803 --> 07:19.270
Jeremy's going to fix you.

07:19.272 --> 07:21.606
He's going to be okay, right?
(Soft grunts)

07:21.608 --> 07:24.442
Nick, let's get him up on the table.

07:24.444 --> 07:26.644
(Mixed grunts)

07:28.813 --> 07:30.414
Elena: What happened?

07:30.416 --> 07:33.083
These two guys, they... broke
into the house. Logan hid me.

07:33.085 --> 07:36.386
Marsten and LeBlanc.
We had to come here.

07:36.388 --> 07:38.055
You did the right thing.

07:38.057 --> 07:40.257
I'm going to have to draw
some fluid out of his chest

07:40.259 --> 07:41.892
so that his lung can expand.

07:41.894 --> 07:44.427
You can put a needle in his lungs?
He's in good hands.

07:44.429 --> 07:45.929
What if he needs surgery?

07:45.931 --> 07:48.632
You know that we can't
involve the police, right?

07:48.634 --> 07:50.267
Hey, Rachel,

07:50.269 --> 07:52.435
why don't we give these
guys some space, okay?

07:52.437 --> 07:54.070
We'll go in the next room. It's okay.

07:54.072 --> 07:55.872
Rachel: No, no. I'm not leaving Logan.

07:55.874 --> 07:57.807
Go with Nick. I'll stay
here and help Jeremy.

07:57.809 --> 07:59.942
It's okay. This way.

08:08.152 --> 08:11.453
Okay, Logan, try to hold your
breath while I do this, okay?

08:17.060 --> 08:18.627
(Groaning in pain)

08:18.629 --> 08:20.629
Okay, okay, okay.

08:21.698 --> 08:23.732
Ahh!
(Panting)

08:23.734 --> 08:26.402
Logan will pull through.

08:26.404 --> 08:28.570
He has a lot to live for.

08:28.572 --> 08:31.206
He told me the good news.

08:31.208 --> 08:33.842
You must be excited.

08:33.844 --> 08:36.511
I was.

08:36.514 --> 08:38.446
But now, with all this, I mean...

08:38.448 --> 08:40.849
What am I bringing this child into?

08:43.318 --> 08:45.687
You're bringing a child
into a loving family

08:45.689 --> 08:47.655
with the man that you adore.

08:48.925 --> 08:52.027
As for what's happening with our family,

08:52.029 --> 08:55.396
we can protect you until it's all over.

08:55.398 --> 08:57.332
You and your child.

08:57.334 --> 08:59.834
We're all real anxious
to meet the little guy.

09:02.771 --> 09:05.039
Logan was shocked about the
whole fatherhood thing.

09:05.041 --> 09:07.875
You and the baby mean the world to him.

09:09.845 --> 09:12.046
And he means everything to me.

09:14.850 --> 09:17.218
Listen to me, Rachel.

09:19.821 --> 09:22.756
Logan will pull through, okay?

09:22.758 --> 09:24.325
You're safe here at Stonehaven.

09:24.327 --> 09:26.960
Do you think that,

09:26.962 --> 09:28.829
after all this,

09:28.831 --> 09:31.164
Logan and I can go back
to our normal lives?

09:32.667 --> 09:34.368
The way things were before?

09:34.370 --> 09:36.002
Things will never be the same.

09:38.473 --> 09:41.775
But that's what happens
when you have a baby.

09:46.713 --> 09:49.883
That should relieve
some of the pressure.

09:49.885 --> 09:51.284
How do you feel, Logan?

09:51.286 --> 09:55.889
(Exhaling)
I can breathe.

09:55.891 --> 09:58.191
I'm sorry I brought Rachel here.

09:58.193 --> 09:59.392
We had no choice.

09:59.394 --> 10:01.360
I understand.

10:01.362 --> 10:03.829
You did what you had to do.

10:03.831 --> 10:05.264
For now.

10:07.834 --> 10:10.536
I'm going to get you to the
infirmary so you can rest.

10:10.538 --> 10:12.170
We need you healthy.

10:12.172 --> 10:15.672
( ♪ )

10:19.446 --> 10:21.146
Wake up.
(Thud)

10:21.148 --> 10:24.116
It's a new day and we have
some catching up to do.

10:24.118 --> 10:26.184
(Growling)

10:26.186 --> 10:28.186
Santos: There's some things
that I need to know.

10:28.188 --> 10:31.356
Perhaps you may want to ask some
actual questions this time.

10:31.358 --> 10:33.892
Just a thought.

10:33.894 --> 10:35.660
I've been waiting for years

10:35.662 --> 10:38.630
to get my vengeance
on the Danvers family.

10:38.632 --> 10:40.732
Every dog has his day, Karl.

10:40.734 --> 10:42.199
Let me have mine.

10:42.201 --> 10:43.735
Yes, yes.

10:43.737 --> 10:45.202
He killed your brother and
ruined your childhood.

10:45.204 --> 10:48.239
Nothing a good therapist won't fix.

10:48.241 --> 10:50.507
But this nonsense, is
it really necessary?

10:50.509 --> 10:52.376
Yes. Definitely.

10:52.378 --> 10:55.947
(Screaming)

10:55.949 --> 10:57.581
Ho-oh!

10:57.583 --> 11:00.151
Feeling spunky this morning?

11:00.153 --> 11:03.087
Fortunately, Thomas here has
just the thing for that.

11:07.926 --> 11:10.260
(Grunting)

11:23.174 --> 11:25.175
(Soft ♪)

11:25.177 --> 11:28.677
( ♪ )

11:33.418 --> 11:35.952
(Cell phone buzzing)

11:39.237 --> 11:41.557
(Whispering) I've been trying to
reach you since yesterday.

11:41.559 --> 11:43.325
I know. I'm sorry.

11:43.327 --> 11:44.994
How is he?

11:44.996 --> 11:46.929
Diane: <i>The doctor says he's
going to be all right.</i>

11:46.931 --> 11:50.099
He's just resting now.

11:50.101 --> 11:51.300
Are you okay?

11:51.302 --> 11:52.535
Yeah, I'm fine.

11:52.537 --> 11:54.537
(Sigh)
Thank God.

11:54.539 --> 11:56.005
Elena, where the hell are you?

11:58.475 --> 12:00.575
Have you spoken to him?

12:00.577 --> 12:02.044
About what happened?

12:02.046 --> 12:04.880
Yes. He doesn't remember much.

12:04.882 --> 12:08.050
You should be here with him.

12:08.052 --> 12:09.318
Which hospital?

12:09.320 --> 12:11.286
We're on the post-op
floor, Toronto General,

12:11.288 --> 12:12.854
room 718.

12:14.690 --> 12:16.324
Be there as soon as I can.

12:16.326 --> 12:19.826
( ♪ )

13:06.340 --> 13:08.108
Elena!

13:08.110 --> 13:10.311
I know that you would do
anything you could to help Clay.

13:10.312 --> 13:11.911
Santos asked to meet me.

13:18.052 --> 13:19.886
You know I can't let you do that.

13:22.022 --> 13:23.957
(Grunting)

13:23.959 --> 13:26.993
Let me go! Please, I have to save him!

13:26.995 --> 13:28.761
(Grunting)

13:28.763 --> 13:30.529
- You're locking me in?
- Until this is done.

13:30.531 --> 13:33.099
Jeremy, I was trying to save Clay!

13:33.101 --> 13:35.000
So am I.

13:35.002 --> 13:37.903
And I cannot let you compromise
my negotiations with Santos.

13:37.905 --> 13:39.771
Please don't do this.

13:39.773 --> 13:43.309
I let you go to Toronto because I
thought that you would be safe.

13:43.311 --> 13:45.010
And I was wrong.

13:45.012 --> 13:48.114
And I know that you would
do anything to help Clay.

13:48.116 --> 13:50.716
The only place that I can
keep you safe is in here.

13:50.718 --> 13:52.951
I know what you're doing, Jeremy.

13:52.953 --> 13:55.286
You think if you offer yourself
for Clay, you can end this.

13:55.288 --> 13:57.589
But you can't trust Santos.

13:57.591 --> 13:59.992
He could kill you and Clay.

14:03.395 --> 14:05.697
I know.

14:05.699 --> 14:07.499
I don't trust Santos.

14:09.468 --> 14:13.304
But right now the most important
thing for me is to protect you.

14:13.306 --> 14:14.739
From yourself.

14:17.943 --> 14:20.077
Nick and I will deal with this.

14:26.584 --> 14:28.653
Jeremy!

14:28.655 --> 14:30.521
Let me out of here!

14:34.159 --> 14:36.093
(Panting)

14:41.330 --> 14:44.830
( ♪ )

14:49.928 --> 14:51.895
Hey, babe.

14:51.897 --> 14:53.964
(Grunting)

14:53.966 --> 14:55.765
How are you feeling?

14:55.767 --> 14:58.201
Ohh... better.

14:58.203 --> 15:00.803
How are you holding up?

15:00.805 --> 15:03.473
I'm okay, given the circumstances.

15:04.876 --> 15:07.143
- Nick says that we're safe here.
- He's right.

15:07.145 --> 15:09.178
Then why don't I feel safe?

15:09.180 --> 15:11.681
Those people that attacked us,

15:11.683 --> 15:13.416
they can't hurt us here.

15:13.418 --> 15:15.217
So, what?

15:15.219 --> 15:18.354
We're supposed to live here
for the rest of our lives?

15:18.356 --> 15:23.325
When I'm able, we'll go.

15:23.327 --> 15:25.694
We'll go far away, okay?

15:31.501 --> 15:33.269
It won't be long before Elena and I

15:33.271 --> 15:35.037
walk off into the sunset together.

15:35.039 --> 15:36.872
It'll never happen.

15:36.874 --> 15:40.276
Oh, it'll happen.

15:40.278 --> 15:43.344
You just won't be around to see it.

15:43.346 --> 15:47.048
You've always been a very
loyal Pack member, Clayton.

15:47.050 --> 15:50.819
Always doing Jeremy's bidding.

15:50.821 --> 15:53.988
Like when you killed my brother.

15:53.990 --> 15:56.057
Let me ask you:

15:56.059 --> 15:58.092
how did it feel to kill Stephen

15:58.094 --> 16:00.261
at Jeremy's behest?

16:00.263 --> 16:02.496
As good as it will when I kill you.

16:02.498 --> 16:03.998
Hm.

16:04.000 --> 16:05.766
Wrong answer.
(Grunts)

16:05.768 --> 16:09.003
Which families are currently
aligned with the Pack?

16:09.005 --> 16:10.405
All of them.

16:12.607 --> 16:14.608
What's the status on Jeremy's injuries?

16:14.610 --> 16:18.045
Is he fully recovered from our
little roadside surprise?

16:18.047 --> 16:20.113
Strong enough to take on Koenig

16:20.115 --> 16:22.450
with enough left to kick your ass.

16:22.452 --> 16:23.751
(Grunt)

16:23.753 --> 16:25.853
The Pack is falling apart

16:25.855 --> 16:27.655
and we both know it.

16:27.657 --> 16:31.524
The only thing left in your
future is more of this.

16:33.428 --> 16:36.196
You're getting carried away, Daniel.

16:36.198 --> 16:40.033
This has nothing to do
with bringing down Jeremy.

16:40.035 --> 16:41.668
This has everything to do with a history

16:41.670 --> 16:44.571
of you watching Clay get
everything you ever wanted:

16:44.573 --> 16:46.739
status in the Pack...

16:46.741 --> 16:48.942
(Scoffs)
and the girl.

16:54.949 --> 16:56.616
Tick-tock.

16:56.618 --> 16:58.885
Time is running out on you.

16:58.887 --> 17:00.386
The girl and I

17:00.388 --> 17:02.722
have a lunch date this afternoon.

17:02.724 --> 17:04.790
You know, I've been keeping
a close eye on Elena

17:04.791 --> 17:06.959
these past few weeks.

17:06.961 --> 17:09.362
You should have seen her at
Philip's sister's wedding.

17:09.364 --> 17:12.999
Trying to lead a normal life.

17:13.001 --> 17:15.367
But you and I both know

17:15.369 --> 17:17.435
that isn't really Elena.

17:17.438 --> 17:19.738
I bet she'd give it all up
just to save you.

17:19.740 --> 17:23.340
In fact, I'm counting on it.

17:23.343 --> 17:26.545
Elena doesn't know this yet, but...

17:26.547 --> 17:28.246
when I get my hands

17:28.248 --> 17:31.249
on her perfect body,
(Grunt)

17:31.251 --> 17:33.451
we're going to breed a new generation

17:33.453 --> 17:34.987
of werewolves.

17:34.989 --> 17:37.355
Perfect werewolves.

17:37.357 --> 17:39.424
Our children.

17:39.426 --> 17:41.659
And I anticipate

17:41.661 --> 17:44.962
having a very big family.

17:44.964 --> 17:46.964
We're going to be very, very busy.

17:48.967 --> 17:50.835
She might never leave the bed.

17:50.837 --> 17:53.370
(Grunting)

17:57.075 --> 17:59.343
(Buzzing)
(Grunting, yelling)

18:00.779 --> 18:03.313
(Continued yelling)

18:14.292 --> 18:16.193
You're dehydrated from the blood loss.

18:16.195 --> 18:18.362
Here, drink this.

18:18.364 --> 18:20.064
(Groan)
Where's Rachel?

18:20.066 --> 18:22.266
She's taking a nap in Elena's room.

18:22.268 --> 18:24.935
Just trying to keep her
from wandering around.

18:32.743 --> 18:34.811
Thank you...

18:34.813 --> 18:36.345
for saving my life, Jeremy.

18:37.682 --> 18:40.817
And I'm sorry I wasn't
here when you needed me.

18:40.819 --> 18:42.585
I understand.

18:44.821 --> 18:46.755
(Laugh)

18:46.757 --> 18:48.991
It's been so long since
we've had a little one

18:48.993 --> 18:51.094
roaming the grounds at Stonehaven.

18:52.496 --> 18:54.397
Oh, your life is going to change so much

18:54.399 --> 18:55.931
when you become a father.

18:55.933 --> 18:57.266
You have no idea.

18:57.268 --> 18:59.301
Are you ready for the responsibility?

18:59.303 --> 19:02.071
Well, I've got a few months.

19:05.241 --> 19:08.176
A large part of being a parent

19:08.178 --> 19:11.847
is to make the right
choices for your child.

19:11.849 --> 19:13.548
Be a strong man,

19:13.550 --> 19:16.184
a good role model in his life.

19:16.186 --> 19:18.553
But I promise you, the first time

19:18.555 --> 19:20.589
you look into that child's eyes,

19:20.591 --> 19:23.658
you are going to know that
you would do anything

19:23.660 --> 19:25.994
to keep them safe.

19:25.996 --> 19:27.662
That's what parents do.

19:31.634 --> 19:34.335
Over the centuries,

19:34.337 --> 19:37.672
we've learned that the only
way to keep our kind safe

19:37.674 --> 19:40.742
is within the Pack.

19:40.744 --> 19:42.209
That's it.

19:46.248 --> 19:48.516
I have some business
to attend to in town.

19:51.085 --> 19:53.654
We can continue this conversation later.

19:53.656 --> 19:55.289
I hope.

20:03.731 --> 20:06.266
(Panting)

20:09.570 --> 20:12.005
(Engine ignition)

20:13.074 --> 20:15.208
(Vehicle driving off)

20:18.445 --> 20:20.981
(Grunt of anger)

20:23.984 --> 20:26.118
(Metallic clanking)

20:39.299 --> 20:41.300
(Continued clanking)

20:41.302 --> 20:43.435
(Ominous ♪)

20:43.437 --> 20:46.937
( ♪ )

21:09.995 --> 21:12.597
(Clanking)

21:12.599 --> 21:16.099
( ♪ )

21:34.386 --> 21:36.287
(Gasp)
What are you doing?

21:36.289 --> 21:38.422
I... I heard something.

21:40.726 --> 21:43.761
It's an old house with old pipes.

21:43.763 --> 21:45.262
I grew up in an old house.

21:45.264 --> 21:46.897
That is not the sound of old pipes.

21:46.899 --> 21:49.767
Trust me when I tell you you
do not want to go down there.

21:49.769 --> 21:51.468
Why not?
(Clanking)

21:53.437 --> 21:56.606
Some things you see, you can't un-see.

21:58.376 --> 22:01.844
What's going on down there?

22:01.846 --> 22:04.514
Old pipes.

22:04.516 --> 22:08.050
Now go upstairs and forget all this.

22:29.539 --> 22:31.707
- Get me out of here!
- What are you doing in the cage?

22:31.709 --> 22:33.875
Jeremy didn't want me
to meet with Santos.

22:33.877 --> 22:35.811
So he locked you up?

22:35.813 --> 22:37.846
He didn't tell you?

22:37.848 --> 22:40.182
Jeremy's going to sacrifice
himself to Santos

22:40.184 --> 22:41.983
in exchange for Clay's life.

22:41.985 --> 22:44.953
But I'm afraid he's just
going to kill them both.

22:44.955 --> 22:48.156
All right, now what?

22:48.158 --> 22:50.091
I don't think we're safe here.

22:51.527 --> 22:54.061
You and Rachel need to leave now.

22:57.566 --> 22:59.099
Take care of her.

23:03.739 --> 23:05.940
Daniel Santos might be
the scum of the earth,

23:05.942 --> 23:07.875
but if nothing else, he's punctual.

23:07.877 --> 23:09.777
There's something wrong.

23:09.779 --> 23:11.511
Maybe he clocked us and bolted.

23:11.513 --> 23:14.514
Jeremy: Or maybe this is all
just a ruse to lure us out.

23:14.516 --> 23:16.650
We need to go back to Stonehaven now.

23:23.524 --> 23:25.359
Hey, hey-hey-hey.

23:25.361 --> 23:27.494
You'll get yours, I promise.

23:35.936 --> 23:37.771
You came alone.

23:37.773 --> 23:40.707
That's the second smart
thing you've done.

23:40.709 --> 23:43.042
The first was warning me about
Jeremy and Nick at the diner.

23:43.044 --> 23:46.246
I'm not interested in small talk.

23:46.248 --> 23:48.514
Tell me what it'll take to release Clay.

23:53.509 --> 23:54.553
Where's Clay?

23:54.555 --> 23:56.088
I thought you were going to bring him.

23:56.098 --> 23:58.524
I wasn't going to risk
walking into a Pack ambush.

23:58.774 --> 24:00.367
I needed to ensure that you'd cooperate

24:00.369 --> 24:01.836
before I brought Clay out into the open.

24:01.838 --> 24:03.404
What have you done to him?

24:03.406 --> 24:05.872
Nothing that he hasn't deserved,

24:05.874 --> 24:07.208
for years.

24:10.412 --> 24:12.946
(Grunting)

24:15.650 --> 24:18.185
(Grunts)

24:20.154 --> 24:21.822
If you kill Clay, I swear,

24:21.824 --> 24:24.725
I will hunt you down and make
you wish you were never born.

24:24.727 --> 24:27.761
- Do you understand?
- Yes.

24:33.868 --> 24:35.368
Clay is alive.

24:35.370 --> 24:38.938
And what you do next determines
if he stays that way.

24:38.940 --> 24:40.440
Let's hear your proposition.

24:40.442 --> 24:43.409
The tide has turned against the Pack.

24:43.411 --> 24:45.578
We can attack at will,
as we've demonstrated,

24:45.580 --> 24:48.648
and pretty soon, there won't
be anybody left at Stonehaven

24:48.650 --> 24:50.583
to turn out the lights.

24:50.585 --> 24:51.884
Go on.

24:51.886 --> 24:54.520
You agree to join up with me

24:54.522 --> 24:56.321
and I'll free Clay.

24:56.323 --> 24:58.423
And I'll also let Jeremy

24:58.425 --> 25:00.425
and all the others live,

25:00.427 --> 25:02.728
as long as they agree to
stay on the move like Mutts.

25:02.730 --> 25:04.697
No permanent homes.

25:04.699 --> 25:06.732
- You're serious.
- Deadly.

25:06.734 --> 25:08.233
Oh, and here's the kicker:

25:08.235 --> 25:10.269
if you should ever, ever,

25:10.271 --> 25:12.137
decide to renege on the agreement,

25:12.139 --> 25:14.439
Clay, Jeremy, all of the others,

25:14.441 --> 25:18.009
will be hunted down and slaughtered.

25:18.011 --> 25:20.045
It's a win-win for you.

25:20.047 --> 25:22.314
The people that you love get to live.

25:24.317 --> 25:26.918
And you end up giving
birth to a new dynasty.

25:29.188 --> 25:31.756
Their well-being is in your hands now.

25:33.225 --> 25:35.326
What about everybody else in my life?

25:35.328 --> 25:36.661
You mean Philip?

25:36.663 --> 25:38.262
Well...

25:38.264 --> 25:40.464
Your friend Victor Olson's
gone to pay him a visit,

25:40.466 --> 25:41.799
to finish what he started.

25:41.801 --> 25:43.467
Call him off.

25:43.469 --> 25:45.670
Olson doesn't believe in cell phones.

25:45.672 --> 25:47.705
Hey! I am the only thing

25:47.707 --> 25:49.773
standing between the Pack and death.

25:51.776 --> 25:53.444
So, what'll it be?

26:00.819 --> 26:03.087
My offer's only good
till the end of the day.

26:04.589 --> 26:06.123
Man: I know you've been through a lot.

26:06.125 --> 26:08.391
I just need a minute of your time, okay?

26:08.393 --> 26:10.560
A couple questions, I'll
be out of your hair.

26:10.562 --> 26:13.230
Walk me through what happened.

26:13.232 --> 26:15.031
All I remember were a
couple of guys coming in.

26:15.033 --> 26:16.299
(Deadbolt clattering)

26:16.301 --> 26:18.435
Did you know or recognize them?

26:18.437 --> 26:19.802
No.

26:19.804 --> 26:21.338
They didn't say what they wanted?

26:21.340 --> 26:23.540
They jumped me as soon as they came in.

26:23.542 --> 26:25.074
I tried to put up a fight.

26:25.076 --> 26:27.677
I saw your place. You must
have put up a hell of a fight.

26:27.679 --> 26:29.379
(Grunts)

26:29.381 --> 26:32.749
You got any idea why anyone
would attack you in your home?

26:32.751 --> 26:34.250
I don't have any enemies

26:34.252 --> 26:36.919
if that's what you're getting at.

26:36.921 --> 26:39.088
If you remember anything,

26:39.090 --> 26:40.223
you call me.

26:49.699 --> 26:51.133
You should have told him

26:51.135 --> 26:53.034
about the stalker you
beat up at Elena's show.

26:53.036 --> 26:55.203
That stalker was one of the guys
that attacked me in my apartment.

26:55.205 --> 26:56.905
Why didn't you tell the police that?

26:56.907 --> 26:58.540
Because Elena and her family

26:58.542 --> 27:00.542
are involved in some
kind of a mafia war.

27:00.544 --> 27:01.943
How do you know this?

27:01.945 --> 27:03.746
Elena told me yesterday.

27:03.748 --> 27:05.914
We have got to keep this quiet.

27:05.916 --> 27:08.583
Do not tell Mom when she comes back.

27:08.585 --> 27:11.820
Why are you still protecting Elena?

27:11.822 --> 27:13.822
Especially if it means putting yourself,

27:13.824 --> 27:15.523
and maybe our family, in jeopardy?

27:15.525 --> 27:17.525
Look at me.

27:17.527 --> 27:19.861
Look at where I am.

27:19.863 --> 27:22.963
I'm not saying anything <i>because</i>
it's going to put us in jeopardy.

27:32.174 --> 27:34.676
You look as though you could use a drink.

27:36.812 --> 27:39.814
Sadly, I have nothing
stronger than bottled water.

27:45.253 --> 27:48.189
I wish I could help you more,

27:48.191 --> 27:50.324
but our friend Santos has relegated me

27:50.326 --> 27:52.860
to something above peon status.

27:52.862 --> 27:54.861
Where is he?

27:54.863 --> 27:56.697
He went to meet with Elena.

27:58.399 --> 27:59.666
(Laboured breathing)

27:59.668 --> 28:01.435
It seems your lovely lady

28:01.437 --> 28:04.137
has made quite the
impression on him of late.

28:07.908 --> 28:11.811
This entire affair has
gone horribly sideways

28:11.813 --> 28:13.947
and you should know that...

28:13.949 --> 28:18.051
I never intended for things
to get this far out of hand.

28:18.053 --> 28:20.753
You thought the Pack would
just roll over and play dead?

28:20.755 --> 28:23.522
No.

28:23.524 --> 28:25.691
Let's just say I made
the unfortunate decision

28:25.693 --> 28:27.360
to trade the devil I know in Jeremy

28:27.362 --> 28:29.829
with the devil I don't in Santos,

28:29.831 --> 28:31.530
who's gone from ambitious upstart

28:31.532 --> 28:34.233
to tyrannical despot
in the blink of an eye.

28:35.569 --> 28:37.870
You could always switch sides.

28:37.872 --> 28:40.673
I imagine that's the offer
you made to Zachary Cain,

28:40.675 --> 28:42.475
before you snapped his neck

28:42.477 --> 28:45.410
and buried him amidst the
sugar maples in Stonehaven.

28:47.713 --> 28:49.848
(Wolves snarling on video)

28:56.622 --> 28:58.056
(Snarling)

29:00.426 --> 29:01.860
(Gasp)

29:04.263 --> 29:05.897
(Exhaling)

29:09.935 --> 29:11.703
Look for Logan and Rachel.

29:11.705 --> 29:13.371
- I'll check on Elena.
- Got it.

29:29.721 --> 29:31.255
They're gone too.

29:31.257 --> 29:32.956
There's no sign of struggle,

29:32.958 --> 29:34.958
no scent of Mutt...

29:34.960 --> 29:36.827
Logan must have let her out.

29:38.730 --> 29:41.732
Wherever she is, I hope she
knows what she's doing.

30:05.456 --> 30:07.623
(Grunting)

30:07.625 --> 30:09.492
(Choking)

30:15.167 --> 30:18.002
(Growling)

30:18.004 --> 30:20.404
Tell me where they're holding Clay.

30:23.277 --> 30:25.411
All this rage I had.

30:25.413 --> 30:27.581
Then I see your face,

30:27.583 --> 30:30.383
your beautiful, beautiful face.

30:30.385 --> 30:31.650
Tell me!

30:31.652 --> 30:33.018
Or...?

30:33.020 --> 30:35.921
You'll live to regret it.

30:35.923 --> 30:37.823
I thought we were friends.

30:37.825 --> 30:40.759
We were never friends.

30:40.761 --> 30:42.861
Oh, Elena.

30:42.863 --> 30:46.165
Do you realize how long
we've known each other?

30:46.167 --> 30:48.333
Since you were...

30:48.335 --> 30:51.770
What, six? Seven?

30:51.772 --> 30:54.873
I've been in your life
longer than anyone else.

30:54.875 --> 30:57.910
And after all these years,
I'm still in your life.

30:57.912 --> 30:59.211
Where is he?

30:59.213 --> 31:01.213
If I tell you,

31:01.215 --> 31:03.115
what'll you give me in return?

31:05.718 --> 31:07.285
Your life.

31:09.088 --> 31:12.124
You're not a killer.

31:12.126 --> 31:14.493
You don't know what I am.

31:16.129 --> 31:18.062
Aaaah!

31:18.064 --> 31:19.864
Tell me.

31:19.866 --> 31:23.200
And it's important you call
me back when you get this.

31:23.202 --> 31:25.036
Any word from Logan or Elena?

31:25.038 --> 31:26.337
I've left them messages.

31:26.339 --> 31:28.072
What did your cousin Jorge say?

31:28.074 --> 31:30.842
The grapevine is buzzing that
the Mutts are reaching out,

31:30.844 --> 31:32.543
looking for new recruits.

31:32.545 --> 31:34.211
For what, exactly?

31:34.213 --> 31:36.080
My guess,

31:36.082 --> 31:38.215
an all-out assault.

31:38.217 --> 31:40.050
They know we're weak.

31:40.052 --> 31:42.453
Especially without Clay.

31:42.455 --> 31:44.622
But the more this situation
unfolds, the more I start to wonder

31:44.624 --> 31:46.390
who's really pulling the
strings of this uprising.

31:46.392 --> 31:48.459
You don't think it's Santos.

31:48.461 --> 31:50.827
I think he has the wherewithal

31:50.829 --> 31:52.996
to recruit Cain and Marsten,

31:52.998 --> 31:54.564
bite a couple of killers and pedophiles.

31:54.566 --> 31:57.333
But that's just one aspect of this.

31:57.335 --> 31:59.202
They're hitting Elena from all sides.

31:59.204 --> 32:00.904
Here, in Toronto.

32:00.906 --> 32:03.573
And then this video of Logan and
Elena running as wolves surfaces.

32:03.575 --> 32:05.575
That's not a coincidence.

32:05.577 --> 32:08.745
No, Clay said it came from
somebody named James Williams.

32:08.747 --> 32:10.880
We need to figure out
who James Williams is

32:10.882 --> 32:13.483
and why he's getting
involved in our business.

32:16.920 --> 32:18.221
Time is running out.

32:18.223 --> 32:21.090
For me, or for Clay?

32:23.494 --> 32:25.195
Aaaah!

32:25.197 --> 32:27.129
Tell me where he is and
I'll tie off your wounds

32:27.131 --> 32:30.199
and stop the bleeding.

32:30.201 --> 32:32.001
Such a pretty girl.

32:32.003 --> 32:33.803
Always.

32:33.805 --> 32:38.174
All I'd want is to brush
your hair one more time.

32:38.176 --> 32:39.675
Untie me.

32:39.677 --> 32:41.443
I will.

32:41.445 --> 32:44.680
Once you tell me where he is.

32:44.682 --> 32:46.548
I tell you what I know,

32:46.550 --> 32:51.220
if you promise to let me go.

32:53.523 --> 32:55.056
Fine.

32:55.058 --> 32:57.726
(Door opening)

32:57.728 --> 33:00.261
(Rapid breaths)

33:05.000 --> 33:07.535
(Groaning)

33:13.442 --> 33:15.309
(Whispering)
Not a sound from you.

33:20.449 --> 33:21.949
Philip.

33:21.951 --> 33:23.417
Elena, what are you doing here?

33:23.419 --> 33:26.053
- Did you get my messages?
- I didn't have my cell phone.

33:28.022 --> 33:29.823
- Your life is in danger.
- I believe you.

33:29.825 --> 33:32.293
I just don't know what's the
greater threat, those men or you.

33:32.295 --> 33:36.897
Philip, I tried so hard
to make this work.

33:36.899 --> 33:39.900
To be who you wanted me to be, okay?
Who you deserved.

33:39.902 --> 33:41.869
All I ever wanted from you

33:41.871 --> 33:43.737
was for you to be honest with me.

33:43.739 --> 33:46.740
I know, and you'll never know
how sorry I am for that.

33:49.443 --> 33:52.612
I need you to do me
one last favour, okay?

33:52.614 --> 33:54.180
Please just leave.

33:54.182 --> 33:55.749
Go as far away as you can!

33:55.751 --> 33:58.351
I am not going to let somebody
force me to go on the run.

33:59.987 --> 34:02.722
Once you met me,

34:02.724 --> 34:05.091
and we fell in love,

34:05.093 --> 34:07.726
your life went down a dark road.

34:07.728 --> 34:10.862
Okay, I didn't want that,
but it happened.

34:10.864 --> 34:12.331
Olson: (Groaning)

34:12.333 --> 34:15.567
Philip, I'm trying to
save your life, okay?

34:15.569 --> 34:17.036
Please, just go!

34:17.038 --> 34:18.804
Okay, while you still can.

34:22.909 --> 34:24.943
Please.

34:24.945 --> 34:28.445
( ♪ )

34:49.969 --> 34:52.337
It was all so touching.

34:52.339 --> 34:55.005
You don't want to lose
us both in one day.

34:55.007 --> 34:57.875
You can still save yourself, so talk.

34:57.877 --> 34:59.977
You are in complete control,

34:59.979 --> 35:01.679
and yet,

35:01.681 --> 35:04.014
I know you're still scared of me.

35:04.016 --> 35:06.851
<i>You want to come inside? I've
got more rabbits in there.</i>

35:06.853 --> 35:08.853
I'm not scared.

35:08.855 --> 35:10.321
Not anymore.

35:15.126 --> 35:17.962
They have him in a barn.

35:17.964 --> 35:21.332
A place called Fox Valley Farms.

35:23.168 --> 35:26.270
How do I know I can believe you?

35:26.272 --> 35:30.540
Isn't that the same thing your
dear Philip just asked you?

35:35.847 --> 35:37.146
Hey...

35:37.148 --> 35:38.348
What are you doing?

35:38.350 --> 35:41.084
I told you where Clay is.

35:41.086 --> 35:42.986
Untie me.

35:44.856 --> 35:48.057
You promised me.

35:48.059 --> 35:50.426
(Groaning)

35:50.428 --> 35:51.995
I lied.

35:58.936 --> 36:00.270
(Door slams)

36:10.285 --> 36:11.653
(Sniffing)

36:15.758 --> 36:17.358
(Sniffing)

36:23.765 --> 36:27.265
( ♪ )

36:33.876 --> 36:36.221
Damn it, LeBlanc.

36:36.223 --> 36:38.223
(Grunts)

36:38.225 --> 36:41.725
( ♪ )

36:49.402 --> 36:50.535
Daniel?

36:53.004 --> 36:54.839
(Grunting)

37:02.080 --> 37:03.513
Oh, my God...

37:06.952 --> 37:09.953
Clay, hey.

37:13.791 --> 37:15.892
It's good to see you, darlin'.

37:15.894 --> 37:19.394
( ♪ )

37:23.235 --> 37:25.168
(Sniffing)

37:31.541 --> 37:33.176
(Sniffing)

37:33.178 --> 37:34.543
Elena...

37:34.545 --> 37:38.045
( ♪ )

37:45.723 --> 37:47.490
I'll be right back.

37:47.492 --> 37:50.992
( ♪ )

38:23.935 --> 38:25.235
How is he?

38:25.237 --> 38:28.338
He's a little weak right now.

38:28.340 --> 38:31.341
He's been through a lot.

38:31.343 --> 38:33.143
He's strong, he'll recover.

38:36.713 --> 38:38.982
I spoke to Jorge.

38:38.984 --> 38:42.319
He's sent a team to sanitize
Philip's apartment.

38:42.321 --> 38:44.220
They'll get rid of any
trace of you and Olson.

38:48.024 --> 38:50.259
I am sorry that you were
forced to kill again.

38:51.862 --> 38:53.195
Forced?

38:55.098 --> 38:56.899
He gave me everything I needed,

38:56.901 --> 38:58.367
and still I killed him.

38:58.369 --> 39:01.804
Victor Olson got exactly
what he deserved.

39:01.806 --> 39:03.638
I never wanted to be an executioner.

39:03.640 --> 39:06.442
That's why I didn't
kill Marsten or Santos.

39:08.845 --> 39:11.847
After I saw what they did to
Clay, maybe I should have.

39:11.849 --> 39:14.549
You did what you had to do to save Clay.

39:14.551 --> 39:16.952
Just like he did for you
when you first came here.

39:19.389 --> 39:22.256
Clay bit me and almost killed me.

39:26.028 --> 39:27.863
When Clay first brought
you to Stonehaven,

39:27.865 --> 39:30.131
it was a very...

39:30.133 --> 39:32.166
foolish and impetuous act.

39:34.871 --> 39:37.638
I'd just come back from a run.

39:37.640 --> 39:39.140
And I was in the middle of a Change

39:39.142 --> 39:41.842
when you turned and saw me.

39:41.844 --> 39:43.677
I didn't see anything.

39:49.451 --> 39:51.552
You know I couldn't take that chance.

39:54.689 --> 39:56.624
You thought that I saw you Change,

39:56.626 --> 39:58.358
so you were going to kill me?

40:01.429 --> 40:03.363
I didn't have a choice, Elena.

40:09.370 --> 40:11.571
And Clay bit me to give me
another chance at living.

40:11.573 --> 40:14.107
He defied my orders to save you, yes.

40:16.210 --> 40:20.147
All this time, I blamed
him for ruining my life.

40:24.419 --> 40:26.586
He was always the faithful son.

40:28.422 --> 40:31.323
And he was willing to accept...

40:31.325 --> 40:34.460
my burden to protect the
relationship between you and I.

40:34.462 --> 40:36.663
And you let him carry that?

40:39.800 --> 40:41.968
I... questioned myself every day

40:41.970 --> 40:44.970
whether I should tell you the truth.

40:47.140 --> 40:49.442
I'm sorry, Elena.

40:49.444 --> 40:51.610
I did what I thought
was best for the Pack.

40:51.612 --> 40:55.481
But it wasn't what was
best for me, Jeremy!

40:55.483 --> 40:56.682
Or for Clay!

40:56.684 --> 40:59.384
No, and Clay chose
to make that sacrifice.

41:02.321 --> 41:05.190
Just like you made a
sacrifice to save him.

41:10.463 --> 41:13.699
All this time...

41:13.701 --> 41:16.033
Yeah.

41:16.035 --> 41:18.203
All this time.

41:20.906 --> 41:24.642
Clay has been the most trustworthy
person you've ever known.

41:24.644 --> 41:28.144
( ♪ )

41:39.358 --> 41:40.491
(Sigh)

41:43.361 --> 41:46.861
( ♪ )

42:41.417 --> 42:43.185
We're dead!

42:43.187 --> 42:45.120
- Clayton's going to come after us...
- No, he's going to come after you.

42:45.122 --> 42:47.355
When he's done with you, then
he's going to come after us.

42:47.357 --> 42:48.891
- Let him come.
- Oh, shut up!

42:48.893 --> 42:50.959
You have no idea the
hornet's nest we've kicked.

42:50.961 --> 42:52.294
Clay's weak.

42:52.296 --> 42:55.096
We can still win this battle.

42:55.098 --> 42:57.232
The three of us?
(Cell phone ringing)

43:03.772 --> 43:05.574
Hello?

43:05.576 --> 43:07.709
James: I understand you
lost your trump card.

43:07.711 --> 43:09.911
Santos: (On phone) <i>- How did you know that?</i>
- It doesn't matter.

43:09.913 --> 43:12.513
There will be no more kidnappings,
no more negotiations,

43:12.515 --> 43:14.782
no more talking, period.

43:14.784 --> 43:17.518
It's time for action.

43:17.520 --> 43:19.187
What kind of action?

43:19.189 --> 43:21.555
It's time to storm the castle.

